Quote:  TURBOT (<i>Ammotretis Guntheri</i>). ... [28] In the <i>Transactions of the New Zealand Institute</i> vol. viii., p.215, Captain Hutton writes thus of the <i>Ammotretis rostratus:</i> `A fish not uncommon in the Dunedin market, where it goes by the name of `lemon sole,' agrees so well with Dr. Gunther's description of <i>A. rostratus</i>, from Tasmania, that I have no hesitation in considering it that species.'
