Quote:  AMMOTRETIS NUDIPINNIS Waite. <i>Turbot.</i> A rare fish in each of the four chief towns. I have been informed that it is more common around Invercargill and Stewart Island. ... Distribution: South Island coasts; examples have been taken as far north as Whangarei.
Notes:  Phillipps Notes on the Edible Fishes

